91,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/124842061/75273374","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22944776#t22944776","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22944776#t22944776","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22944776#t22944776","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_3111149","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://plus.google.com/102746494923227506916","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22944776,"talkid":89628,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22944776#t22944776","upictitle":"John Nelson: pic#124842061","article":"This is why I love your blog so much: I learn more about other authors and writers from you than any other source. In particular, female writers doing stuff of cultural relevance (script writing for Star Trek is of he highest cultural relevance). I'm going to proceed to promote the crap about this series now. ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"October 30 2015, 01:20:17 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://plus.google.com/102746494923227506916","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/google-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"John Nelson","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_3111149","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=75273374&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"John Nelson","ctime_ts":1446168017,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22949896#t22949896","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22949896#t22949896","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22949896#t22949896","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"gman109","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://gman109.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22949896,"talkid":89648,"etime_ts":"1446242259","thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22949896#t22949896","above":22944776,"upictitle":"gman109: pic#0","article":"Agreed 100%.<br /><br />I read this blog regularly for both the insight and access to George - few other authors or famous people allow this type of interaction, and to be able to do so with brilliant author(s) is fantastic, and I treat it as a very fortunate privilege - because it is.  <br /><br />Measure of a Man is my favorite TNG episode, more so than the typical \"Inner Light\" which many others favor as their numero uno.  Exceptionally well written and created, and IMO this put Brent Spiner on the radar as a force in terms of his ability.  So much to like in that episode, I can't recommend it highly enough to anyone that has the ability to stream it on Netlix.<br /><br />Snod joining the ranks of the Youtube/etc Star Trek endeavors is a landmark event IMO.  They did well with their first effort out of the gate, but having her writing, vision, and drive with them now - great things will be coming, believe it.<br /><br />I'm a large contributor to the Star Trek Axanar effort now.  Check them out if you haven't, their pilot/prelude is stunning for how much they made it for.<br /><br />It warms me to see former actors participating in these fan and community driven efforts - and now with writers with major horsepower joining in such as Snodgrass, the snowball effect will soon be knocking on the door of CBS/Paramount vis a vis ST IMO.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"October 30 2015, 21:56:30 UTC","parent":22944776,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://gman109.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"gman109","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"gman109","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://gman109.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"etime":"October 30 2015, 21:57:39 UTC","dname":"gman109","ctime_ts":1446242190,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/125210192/70950218","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22945544#t22945544","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22945544#t22945544","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22945544#t22945544","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"cashcraig","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://cashcraig.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22945544,"talkid":89631,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22945544#t22945544","upictitle":"Cash Craig: pic#125210192","article":"I've never seen any Star Trek... but judging by my experience with DOUBLE SOLITAIRE, I'd bet those episodes will be a great wild ride.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"October 30 2015, 03:31:11 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://cashcraig.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"cashcraig","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"cashcraig","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://cashcraig.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"cashcraig","ctime_ts":1446175871,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/123903486/72071300","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22945800#t22945800","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22945800#t22945800","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22945800#t22945800","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_2738803","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://twitter.com/OberynMattell","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22945800,"talkid":89632,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22945800#t22945800","upictitle":"Oberyn Mattell: pic#123903486","article":"This is interesting how it works with the rights and all. I looked it up and CBS owns the rights to Star Trek, do they give permission for them to do this?","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"October 30 2015, 05:32:09 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://twitter.com/OberynMattell","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/twitter-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"OberynMattell","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_2738803","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=72071300&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"OberynMattell","ctime_ts":1446183129,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22956296#t22956296","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22956296#t22956296","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22956296#t22956296","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"gman109","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://gman109.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22956296,"talkid":89673,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22956296#t22956296","above":22945800,"upictitle":"gman109: pic#0","article":"It's complicated, but so far, at least with the Axanar effort which is similar to Renegades, CBS hasn't blocked them or anything.<br /><br />THere is much discussion regarding this over at the Axanar group FB pages and elsewhere, you can find more accurate information there about CBS and whatnot.<br /><br />I do know that the producer (also playing a starship Capt in Axanar) has spoken about fears and concerns of CBS lowering the boom someday.<br /><br />IMO I think that Axanar will have a HUGE release, millions of views and possibly sensational BluRay sales as well.  When $ starts rolling in, I could see CBS acting in some fashion.  They would be wise to act in a fair manner however, as they could also stand to make $ in some form of partnership/rights deal on these independence/fan/etc efforts.  <br /><br />I'm completely in favor of companies, authors, entities, whatever, who own rights to material not being poached.  I do also think there is room for co-operation.  Example, CBS isn't putting a dime into Axanar's production, so if Axanar does become a success endeavor in terms or profit, why sue them when you could work WITH them in the future, and share in that success by giving permission as opposed to withholding it and filing lawsuits.  It's a complicated issue, but again, I favor the laws on protecting work, and also favor positive co-op when there is room for it.<br /><br />","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"November 1 2015, 03:18:52 UTC","parent":22945800,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://gman109.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"gman109","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"gman109","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://gman109.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"gman109","ctime_ts":1446347932,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/125544754/76993950","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22946824#t22946824","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22946824#t22946824","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22946824#t22946824","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_3363832","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://twitter.com/TheTVGod","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22946824,"talkid":89636,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/451592.html?thread=22946824#t22946824","upictitle":"Brian Sherman: pic#125544754","article":"I really enjoyed the first Renegades and having Melinda on the next two can only make it better. If you are a fan of the classic Trek universe it's well worth it to kick in a few dollars to help get these made. ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"October 30 2015, 13:00:42 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Renegades 2 &amp; 3","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://twitter.com/TheTVGod","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/twitter-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"TheTVGod","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_3363832","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=76993950&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"TheTVGod","ctime_ts":1446210042,"tracked":0}]}